definitions.definition: One of several species of fish , typically of the Salmoninae subfamily, brownish above with silvery sides and delicate pinkish-orange flesh; they ascend rivers to spawn .
A meal or dish made from this fish.
A pale pinkish - orange colour , the colour of cooked salmon.
The upper bricks in a kiln which receive the least heat .

main_definition: ( zoology ) One of several species of fish , typically of the Salmoninae subfamily, brownish above with silvery sides and delicate pinkish-orange flesh; they ascend rivers to spawn .
